            {
                "s2_paper_id": "c98676a19e456d2e290891732a3c52a9471416e3",
                "title": "Atomic layer etch process for Nb and Ta using CF4/H2 plasma",
                "year": 2026,
                "venue": "Journal of Vacuum Science &amp; Technology A",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 33,
                "abstract": "Cyclic atomic layer etch (ALE) processes were developed for sputtered Nb and Ta thin films using CF4/H2 ICP plasma and Ar+ irradiation. The processes were investigated as a function of CF4/H2 dose time, Ar+ exposure time, and RF substrate bias. Etch per cycle, synergy, and surface roughness before and after etch are reported. Etch rates were similar for both materials for identical process conditions. A soft-saturated ALE process had etch rates of 0.23\u00b10.02\u2009nm/cycle for Nb and 0.23\u00b10.01\u2009nm/cycle for Ta with a total cycle time of 16\u2009s. Synergies were 87% and >99% for Nb and Ta, respectively. Selectivity to Si is also reported. These processes are promising for real-world devices, which are sensitive to etch-induced damage, such as superconducting resonators.",
                "authors": [
